title: GitHub Saver Setup
tags: [[GettingStarted]]

This wiki is prepared for the built-in TiddlyWiki GitHub saver.

Before first online save:

# Create a GitHub repository.
# Put this `index.html` at the repository root.
# In GitHub repo settings, enable Pages from `main` branch `/root`.
# Create a fine-grained GitHub personal access token with contents read/write access to this repository.
# In this wiki, open Control Panel → Saving → Git Service Saver / GitHub Saver.
# Fill:
#* Username: your GitHub username
#* Password: your token
#* Repository: `owner/repo`
#* Branch: `main`
#* Path: `/`
#* Filename: `index.html`

Security note: the token is stored in browser local storage. Use a token limited to this one repo and revoke it if exposed.
